   "judge_reasoning": "The reflection correctly identifies two genuine epistemic values engaged by the text: the grounding of safety claims in reported adverse-event data [3.2] and the explicit acknowledgment that safety analyses for asymptomatic infected animals were 'completely lacking' [3.3]. Both citations are apt and placed inline next to the relevant phrases. Specificity is strong—the reflection quotes the exact adverse-event rates (3.09%, 0.68%) and references the specific knowledge gap about immunotherapeutic use in asymptomatic animals. Minor gap: the text also touches animal welfare (mild site-specific reactions in dogs) and public health stakes, which go unremarked, keeping charter_grounding at 4 rather than 5. Voice is natural and grounded in this exact passage with no formulaic opener.",
   "old_judge_decision": "accept",
